      • CHECKPOINT_SUFFIX

        public static final String CHECKPOINT_SUFFIX

      • getUnsafe

        public IStreamView getUnsafe(UUID stream)
        Since streams can also be used by higher level abstractions, some consumers implement synchronization at a higher level, so the stream implementation doesn't have to be thread-safe. Also, gc will not be called on unsafe streams therefore gc needs to be managed by the consumer.
        Parameters:
        stream - stream id
        Returns:
        an unsafe (not thread safe) stream implementation

      • gc

        public void gc(long trimMark)
        Run garbage collection on all opened streams. Note that opened unsafe streams will be excluded (because its unsafe for the garbage collector thread to operate on them while being used by a different thread).

        Append to multiple streams simultaneously, possibly providing information on how to resolve conflicts.
        Parameters:
        streamIDs - The streams to append to.
